       :marcus-lean "Yes, but as a follow-up. Web IDE doesn't yet; parity says wait."
       :for-alfred "This wave: sessions are fresh each launch.")
     (:q "Real vim gesture parity — buffers, splits, marks, macros?"
       :marcus-lean "No. The vim mode is 'reasonable-in-a-pinch' not 'full vim.' Kids who want vim installed vim.")
     (:q "Should F1 help become a searchable ,help browser?"
       :marcus-lean "Follow-up — tie to book/search when ready.")
     (:q "Wide-CJK glyph rendering?"
       :marcus-lean "Punt. When Sakura-Curator localises, we'll adopt string-width."))

  :ship-checklist
    ((:done "motoi tui launches in the terminal")
     (:done "Sakura Cherry Tree palette everywhere the eye lands")
     (:done "Feature parity with web IDE for the shared verbs")
     (:done "Ambient completions + ghost-text with Tab-accept")
     (:done "Vim + Emacs + Basic editor modes")
     (:done "Settings menu + Help tab")
     (:done "CPU panel toggle (F4)")
     (:done "Status ribbon + transient flashes")
     (:done "Terminal-idiomatic focus cycling (Tab, F6)")
